{Speech 2}{}{Greetings, I haven't seen you in Klamath before. I'm Aldo, the city greeter. My job is to welcome every newcomer to town and answer any questions they might have about our little bucolic town. Welcome to Klamath. What may I call you?}
{Speech 2 Answer 5}{}{Mmm, thanks for the welcome. I'm @sex@|just a traveler|just a traveler|.}
{Speech 2 Answer 4}{}{My name is @pname@, thanks for the hospitality.}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{Just call me - @sex@|the Tough Guy|the Tough Gal| @pname@.}
{Speech 2 Answer 8}{}{You don't need to know my name or anything else about me. Get lost, you dirty drunk.}
{Speech 3}{}{@pname@, you must be a very important and powerful person among your people. Surely one of your great figures would be happy to follow our tradition of rewarding the city greeter.}
{Speech 3 Answer 8}{}{A little advice for you - stay away from the booze for a while.}
{Speech 3 Answer 6}{}{Advice, huh? Well, I figure 5 bucks should be enough to get you off my back.}
{Speech 3 Answer 6*}{}{I wouldn't @sex@|want|want| to go against tradition. Is 5 bucks enough?}
{Speech 3 Answer 8*}{}{You'd better give me advice so I don't @sex@|waste|waste| my time ridding Klamath of your dirty mug.}
{Speech 3 Answer 8**}{}{Sorry, I can't spare you any money.}
{Speech 4}{}{@pname@, since you're new here, and you look like you'd @sex@|want|want| to make use of the signposts, I'll tell you that traditionally you're supposed to tip the greeter before asking questions and so on.}
{Speech 4 Answer 8}{}{A little advice for you - stay away from the booze for a while.}
{Speech 4 Answer 6}{}{Advice, huh? Well, I figure 5 bucks should be enough to get you off my back.}
{Speech 4 Answer 6*}{}{I wouldn't @sex@|want|want| to go against tradition. Is 5 bucks enough?}
{Speech 4 Answer 8*}{}{You'd better give me advice so I don't @sex@|waste|waste| my time ridding Klamath of your dirty mug.}
{Speech 4 Answer 8**}{}{Sorry, I can't spare you any money.}
{Speech 5}{}{All right @sex@|stranger|stranger|, since you're new here, you probably don't know that the greeter is usually rewarded before you ask questions and so on.}
{Speech 5 Answer 8}{}{A little advice for you - stay away from the booze for a while.}
{Speech 5 Answer 6}{}{Advice, huh? Well, I figure 5 bucks should be enough to get you off my back.}
{Speech 5 Answer 6*}{}{I wouldn't @sex@|want|want| to go against tradition. Is 5 bucks enough?}
{Speech 5 Answer 8*}{}{You'd better give me advice so I don't @sex@|waste|waste| my time ridding Klamath of your dirty mug.}
{Speech 5 Answer 8**}{}{Sorry, I can't spare you any money.}
{Speech 6}{}{Thanks for the money, my friend. I'll spend it on medicine for my parched throat. Consider yourself officially @sex@|welcomed|welcomed| to the town of Klamath. Any questions about our wonderful capital?}
{Speech 6 Answer 15}{}{No thanks, I think I'll @sex@|figure|figure| it all out myself.}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{All right, I'd like to ask a couple of questions.}
{Speech 7}{}{Ask away, oh @sex@|my benefactor|my benefactress|.}
{Speech 7 Answer 9}{}{What do folks do here in Klamath?}
{Speech 7 Answer 11}{}{Where can I sell or buy things, or find a healer?}
{Speech 7 Answer 17}{}{Where do you buy your booze?}
{Speech 7 Answer 15}{}{Thanks, I think that's all I @sex@|wanted|wanted| to know for now.}
{Speech 8}{}{Don't mention it. I hope you won't stay in town too long. We don't need the likes of you around here. Hm. Savages - they're all the same.}
{Speech 9}{}{Here in Klamath some people farm, others raise brahmin, but gecko hunting is what most folks do.}
{Speech 9 Answer 10}{}{What's a gecko?}
{Speech 9 Answer 15}{}{Oh, thanks. I think that's all I need to know.}
{Speech 9 Answer 7}{}{That's interesting. I have one more question.}
{Speech 10}{}{A gecko is a big lizard that's hunted around here for its meat and hide. But to catch them you have to do a hell of a lot of work - and it's dangerous too. My advice to a friend... stay away from them. Too much work.}
{Speech 10 Answer 15}{}{Thanks. I think that's all I need to know.}
{Speech 10 Answer 7}{}{Hmm. One more thing, Aldo.}
{Speech 11}{}{You can sell or buy things at Buckner's House or the Golden Gecko. Sometimes they even have healing herbs - not the ones they usually give me to cure myself. The owners are real misers.\n Take a little bit on the tip of a knife and head out, into the cold and rain.}
{Speech 11 Answer 15}{}{Thanks for the information, that's all I @sex@|wanted|wanted| to know.}
{Speech 11 Answer 7}{}{I always @sex@|thought|thought| fresh air was invigorating. Hm, I have one more question for you.}
{Speech 12}{}{I know you @sex@|couldn't|couldn't| give money to the official city greeter before, but maybe this time you feel more @sex@|generous|generous| and @sex@|ready|ready| for an official welcome in Klamath.}
{Speech 12 Answer 6}{}{I suppose I @sex@|could|could| give you 5 bucks to get you off my back.}
{Speech 12 Answer 6*}{}{I @sex@|felt|felt| from the start that we forgot something. Here's 5 bucks. @sex@|Ready|Ready| to be @sex@|welcomed|welcomed|.}
{Speech 12 Answer 16}{}{No, thanks. I don't think I need that.}
{Speech 12 Answer 14}{}{I think it's better to introduce your guts to my sword.}
{Speech 12 Answer 31}{}{Aldo, I want to leave a notice on Maida's board.}
{Speech 12 Answer 32}{}{Aldo, I want to leave a notice on Maida's board.}
{Speech 13}{}{Hey, friend, how good to see you again. Couldn't you @sex@|spare|spare| me some money for a dose of medicine? My throat gets drier by the hour. I can't even make another official greeting.}
{Speech 13 Answer 6}{}{Of course, I can always give 5 bucks to heal a friend.}
{Speech 13 Answer 16}{}{Sorry, Aldo. I can't right now.}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{I think you've had enough medicine. You ought to do some good hard work so the poison comes out of you with the sweat.}
{Speech 13 Answer 31}{}{Aldo, I want to leave a notice on Maida's board.}
{Speech 13 Answer 32}{}{Aldo, I want to leave a notice on Maida's board.}
{Speech 14}{}{Don't mention it. How can you be cruel to such a weak man as me? Damned savages! [Aldo spits on the ground at your feet, drool dangling from his dirty chin]}
{Speech 15}{}{I'm sure the nobility you've shown to someone as useful as me will bring you luck. I hope to see you again soon.}
{Speech 16}{}{I'd surely spend some money on medicine. I feel completely weakened - but if you can't give me anything, I'll understand. Maybe next time, if I'm still around by then.}
{Speech 17}{}{You say you really need medicine? I used to buy it at the Golden Gecko or Buckner's House, they wouldn't sell it to me until I paid off my tab. Luckily for me, Whisky Bob healed his friends up a little.}
{Speech 17 Answer 15}{}{I'm @sex@|glad|glad| you found a place where you can get healed. I think that's all I @sex@|wanted|wanted| to know.}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{Interesting. Where can I find Whisky Bob?}
{Speech 17 Answer 7}{}{Thanks, Aldo. Tell me something else.}
{Speech 18}{}{Whisky Bob is usually at Buckner's, right here in the center of town. He's got a little distillery not far from here.}
{Speech 18 Answer 15}{}{Thanks for the information, Aldo. That's all I @sex@|wanted|wanted| to know.}
{Speech 18 Answer 7}{}{@sex@|Glad|Glad| you found your supplier. Hm, could you breathe a little downward? I want to ask you something else.}
{Speech 19}{}{Hi there, friend - you look a little @sex@|confused|confused|. The one thing you really need here is a friend. I'm Aldo, the city greeter.}
{Speech 19 Answer 20}{}{Friend? He - he... @pname@ as a friend.}
{Speech 19 Answer 14}{}{Oops, you stink. Get out of here.}
{Speech 20}{}{If you give me 20 bucks I'll become your friend and make everyone here your friend too. That's how it works in the big city.}
{Speech 20 Answer 14}{}{Twen-tyyy? Yeah? Big swindler?}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Friend? Here!}
{Speech 21}{}{There you go. Now everyone here, including me, are your big friends, dum... uhh.. friend.}
